TITLE: All It Took AUTHOR: Lara SUMMARY: The decision was made in a split second, and that was all it took. WORD COUNT: 194 CHARACTERS/PAIRING: Don't want to give it away... (Angel characters) RATING: FRT WARNING: Character death, vampirism SPOILERS: AU Angel Season 3. DISCLAIMER: I only wish I were as successful as Joss Whedon. He and Mutant Enemy own this; I just write fanfic for fun. DISTRIBUTION: If anyone wants to archive this, please let me know! FEEDBACK: Very much appreciated. AUTHOR'S NOTES: For 's "all it took" prompt. All it took was slicing his fangs into her neck.

TITLE: Selected Excerpts from the Journals of Rupert Giles AUTHOR: Lara () SUMMARY: Journals from right after Giles' time as Ripper in London. RATING: FRT (for British swearing) CHARACTER/FANDOM: Rupert Giles/Buffy the Vampire Slayer WORD COUNT: ~910 AUTHOR'S NOTES: Written for 's 005. Journal prompt where I play . "Selected Excerpts from the Journals of Rupert Giles"

TITLE: Buttoned Up AUTHOR: Lara () SUMMARY: Wesley helps Giles after he's hurt while trying to keep Dawn away from Glory. PAIRING: Giles/Wesley FANDOM: Buffy the Vampire Slayer RATING: FRT WORD COUNT: 524 SPOILERS: Spoilers through end of Season 5 of BtVS. DISCLAIMER: I only wish I were as successful as Joss Whedon. He and Mutant Enemy own this; I just write fanfic for fun. DISTRIBUTION: If anyone wants to archive this, please let me know! FEEDBACK: Very much appreciated. AUTHOR'S NOTES: A little bit of h/c for since she's sick herself though I think it took a bit of a turn in there. *snugs* Get better, sweetie. Buttoned Up
Don't know if anyone is interested, but I posted a list of favorite older fics of mine on .

Buffy the Vampire Slayer/Angel "Genuine" [Giles/Jenny - AU - FRC] "When..." [Fred/Lilah - AU - FRM] "Going Home" [Wesley/Giles - AU - FRAO] "Want" [Fred/Giles - vamp!AU - FRAO] "Insomnia Cures" [Fred/Giles - AU - FRT] "Their Triangle" [Wesley/Fred/Giles - AU - FRT] "Tell Him" [Wesley/Fred, Spike - GF - FRT] Finished Book 1 of "The Meaning of Heroes" [Wesley/Fred/Giles - AU - FRAO - cowritten with Jess] Heroes "Addiction" [Peter/Isaac - AU - FRAO] Battlestar Galactica "Real Enough" [Six/Gaius - GF - FRT] That's more than I actually thought I did this year. Guess we'll see what I do this coming year. I'm also considering posting a link list of my favorite older fics that I've written since a number of them were written before I had many people on my flist.
